Get a random vector of species names.

Family and order names come from the APG plant names list. Genus and species names come from Theplantlist.org.

names_list(rank = "genus", size = 10)

Arguments

rank
Taxonomic rank, one of species, genus (default), family, order.
size
Number of names to get. Maximum depends on the rank.

Value

Vector of taxonomic names.

Examples

names_list()
#>  [1] "Astelma"     "Androsace"   "Sphaeroma"   "Biscutella"  "Jadunia"    
#>  [6] "Aegiphila"   "Astracantha" "Melanthera"  "Melampyrum"  "Axonopus"   
names_list('species')
#>  [1] "Rubus edeesii"            "Kielmeyera decipines"    
#>  [3] "Narcissus cadevallii"     "Rhodoxylon floridum"     
#>  [5] "Fissidens subundatus"     "Silene miniata"          
#>  [7] "Frankenia speciosa"       "Bousigonia angustifolia" 
#>  [9] "Chiropetalum gymnadenium" "Cecropia idroboi"        
names_list('genus')
#>  [1] "Mikania"           "Aspasia"           "Zygodon"          
#>  [4] "Weberbauerocereus" "Urtica"            "Bohadschia"       
#>  [7] "Desmos"            "Melilotus"         "Eria"             
#> [10] "Cymbidium"        
names_list('family')
#>  [1] "Pimpinellaceae"  "Delimaceae"      "Asclepiadaceae"  "Dactylanthaceae"
#>  [5] "Blakeaceae"      "Luxemburgiaceae" "Nicotianaceae"   "Roridulaceae"   
#>  [9] "Ortegaceae"      "Nyssaceae"      
names_list('order')
#>  [1] "Vochysiales"     "Lentibulariales" "Cistales"        "Metteniusales"  
#>  [5] "Anthemidales"    "Asarales"        "Hydnorales"      "Nolanales"      
#>  [9] "Hamamelidales"   "Ternstroemiales"
names_list('order', '2')
#> [1] "Ephedrales"  "Lonicerales"
names_list('order', '15')
#>  [1] "Didymelales"   "Calycanthales" "Hippuridales"  "Eriocaulales" 
#>  [5] "Nyctaginales"  "Elaeocarpales" "Agavales"      "Gordoniales"  
#>  [9] "Sabiales"      "Nyssales"      "Veratrales"    "Balsaminales" 
#> [13] "Flacourtiales" "Atriplicales"  "Meliales"     

# You can get a lot of genus or species names if you want
nrow(theplantlist)
#> [1] 10000
